It was a pleasure meeting and

know we have drifted apart a bit since
the acquisition (as you predicted) and
we have been quiet in reaching out, but
I thought it made sense now. As you
know, we completed the acquisition of
Shift4 a little over a year ago. We did
this because we felt it was a great
return on capital for the enterprise, it
checked a number of strategic boxes
knowing First Data's weaknesses and
it gave us a plan B in worst case
scenarios. It has worked out very well.

From: J. I.

We have made many

when the numbers or strategic rationale
expire. Lighthouse is important to us.
We can get our arms around the labor
synergies since, at scale, much of it is
performed in Eastern Europe. We also
have good perspective on the software
revenue and attrition in that business
from Vantiv.
